    pearls: ["A cup-to-disc ratio >0.5 or asymmetry >0.2 between eyes warrants glaucoma workup with tonometry and visual field testing","Papilledema (bilateral disc swelling) is a medical emergency suggesting elevated intracranial pressure -- obtain urgent neuroimaging before lumbar puncture","Diabetic retinopathy is the leading cause of blindness in working-age adults; screen annually with dilated exam starting at type 2 DM diagnosis","Hypertensive retinopathy grading: Grade I (arteriolar narrowing), Grade II (AV nicking), Grade III (hemorrhages/exudates), Grade IV (papilledema)","A relative afferent pupillary defect (RAPD/Marcus Gunn pupil) on swinging flashlight test indicates optic nerve or severe retinal disease on the affected side","Cotton-wool spots represent retinal nerve fiber layer infarcts and are seen in diabetes, hypertension, HIV, and lupus"],
